args: Step up, Taro! You and me are\nabout to go round and round!
Wait! You want to DUEL with me?!\nBut I have no idea what I'm doing!
Er, that is to say, as I am still in training,\nI would be little match for you in a true\ncontest of steel, Yachiyo.
Well then, what if we don't use the ol'\npokers? How's that strike you?
So you want to duel...without swords?\nWhat kind of duel is that?

We both polish fast as the dickens, and the
one who hits a mirror shine first walks off
with the brass ring! Seems fairer than me
putting the hurt on you, eh, pal?
Well, I certainly stand a better chance,\nbut I've already finished taking care\nof my armor for the day.
Thought that might be the case,\nwhich is why I borrowed THIS set\nof ragamuffin armor from ol' Malka!
No reason to turn me down now, chum!\nSo whaddya say? A duel to the dazzle?\nA battle of brushes? A clean sweep?
Cat's pajamas! Now then, on your mark!\nGet set!
No time to bump gums, baby! We're in the\nmiddle of a duel to see who can get their\narmor polished up lickety-split.
Well, I'll be a copper's bunions!\nWe finished at the same time.
Oh, wow. Looks like it's a draw.
If you look closely at your visor, Yachiyo,\nyou will find a few unpolished edges.
Well, toss me from the tracks! It's true!
Um, but it's still pretty much all shiny,\nso I'm okay calling it a draw.
Nope! You gave me the bum's rush fair\nand square. Can't have a duel without a\nwinner and a loser, after all.
Yachiyo speaks the truth.\nBear this victory with pride, Taro.
Your daily diligence in armor polishing\nis clearly starting to pay off.
Well, my father gave it to me and all,\nso taking care of it just feels right.
And why, exactly, did you challenge\nhim to this particular contest, Yachiyo?
Ain't it obvious? So I could get even\nstronger than I am now!
It's like my dear ol' grandpappy said:\nYou ain't the strongest until you best a\nthousand opponents in a thousand duels.
Yes, I remember him saying that, but I fail\nto see how it relates to armor polishing.
'Cause I felt like polishing my armor, see?
So I figured making a duel outta it\nwas just more efficient-like.
Yeah, I don't understand it eitherâ€”but I\nDO understand wanting to polish armor.
Whenever I'm lost or worried, polishing my\narmor makes this curious calm come over\nme, almost like I'm polishing my heart.
Incidentally, you've got a really nice suit\nof armor there, Yachiyo.
You normally dress in the bare minimum\nof necessary equipment, so I figured you\npreferred mobility over defense.
My grandpappy gave me this here\narmor as a gift.
I got no fear of the grave, which means\nI try to strike palookas fast and hard.

But now that I know the Mukuroshu are
behind Grandpappy's death, I thought I'd
put this here armor on and have me a
little vengeance hootenanny.
A way of thinking very like you.
But based on the way you are speaking,\nit sounds to me like you do not know who\noriginally gave this armor to you.
Hold it, bub! Are you saying this fine suit\nhere DIDN'T come from Grandpappy?
No. Originally, that armor was a gift\nfrom your sister, Momoyo.
Honest, Saiga, I'm a little worried about\nYachiyo walking the path of the sword.
She has real talent, but that only makes\nthe chances of her being injured rise.
Such worries would do little more\nthan encumber her on the path.
There is no sin in hoping for Yachiyo's\nsafety; do not devalue your love for her.
Thank you, Saiga. In that case, I'm going\nto give her an unequaled piece of armor\nthat will hopefully keep her safe.
Doing so will help to alleviate my worries\nwhile also not causing her any grief.
Your armor is imbued with your sister's\nlove, Yachiyo. That's great!
Alas, she departed this world before\nshe was able to give it to you.
I suspect your grandfather did not inform\nyou of its actual origin in order to spare\nyou any further pain or sadness.
Why do you aim to grow stronger, Yachiyo?
And once you have defeated a thousand\nsouls in duels? What will you do then?
Momoyo did not carry a weapon as you\nand I do, but she was strong nonetheless.
She never wore her anxiety or fear openly.\nShe was ever courageous. Stout of heart.
She only sought the strength to watch\nover us for our sakes.
The strength to watch over us, eh?
You chose the strength of the sword,\nbut for what purpose do you seek it?

Once you come to understand that, you will
be able to grow stronger without charging
headlong from one duel to the next.
You will be given the gift of time.
Oh, that is SO cool! I'm gonna keep trying\nto get stronger too, so let's make sure we\nboth do the best we can together!
(You realized I've been as worried as a\nlong-tailed cat in a room full of rockers\nlately, didn't you, Saiga?)
(But why do I wanna get stronger...?)
